category: SAY IT IN LATIN
category comment: 

clue: You know, in good faith or the real deal, like a rock star; with an "S" at the end, it means your credentials

response: bona fides

clue: This cool Latin phrase means "intrinsically" or "by itself"

response: per se

clue: As a legal term, this 3-word phrase can be a status prohibiting a diplomat to enter a foreign country

response: persona non grata

clue: Literally "without which not", this phrase means "a necessity"

response: sine qua non

clue: Q.E.D. is short for this, meaning "which was to be demonstrated"

response: quod erat demonstrandum

